The paper presents a deterministic distributed algorithm for edge coloring in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves hypergraph maximal matching, which is a combinatorial problem related to graph theory, so cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions approximation algorithms and graph orientations, which fall under cs.AL (Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents a significant improvement over previous results, which is of interest to the theoretical computer science community, so cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a possible sub-category.
